  "obverse": {
    "description": "Yaroslav the Wise was a Grand Duke of Kyiv (1019-1054). In times of his ruling the “Rus' Justice” Code of the Old Rus was composed and adopted, the Christianity was finally established in Rus and the culture developed. Yaroslav the Wise was buried in the Cathedral of St. Sophia in Kyiv.",
    "lettering": "НАЦІОНАЛЬНИЙ БАНК УКРАЇНИ\r\nГОЛОВА\r\n2\r\n...якщо будете жити в любові між собою,\r\nБог буде у вас...\r\nЯРОСЛАВ МУДРИЙ\r\n2\r\n2\r\nДВІ ГРИВНІ",
    "lettering_scripts": [
      {
        "name": "Cyrillic"
      }
    ],
    "lettering_translation": "NATIONAL BANK OF UKRAINE\r\nHEAD\r\n2\r\n...if you live in love with one another,\r\nGod will be with you...\r\nYAROSLAV THE WISE\r\n2\r\n2\r\nTWO HRYVNIAS",
    "picture": "https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/ukraine/626e4ff0a3b293.02902502-original.jpg",
    "thumbnail": "https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/ukraine/626e4ff0a3b293.02902502-180.jpg",
    "picture_copyright": "hex7ech",
    "picture_license_name": "CC BY-NC",
    "picture_license_url": "https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/deed.en"
  },
  "reverse": {
    "description": "The Cathedral of St. Sophia in Kyiv is a historical, architectural and wall painting monument of the first half of the XI century, which is famous worldwide. It was built in the golden age of Kyivan Rus to become the metropolitan's cathedral, i.e. the principal church of Rus, on the place, where Yaroslav had won a victory over Pechenegs. Yaroslav founded therein the first library in Rus.",
    "lettering": "ДВІ ГРИВНІ\r\nНАЦІОНАЛЬНИЙ БАНК УКРАЇНИ\r\n2\r\nСОБОР СВЯТОЇ СОФІЇ\r\n2005\r\n2",
    "lettering_scripts": [
      {
        "name": "Cyrillic"
      }
    ],
    "lettering_translation": "TWO HRYVNIAS\r\nNATIONAL BANK OF UKRAINE\r\n2\r\nST. SOPHIA CATHEDRAL\r\n2005\r\n2",
    "picture": "https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/ukraine/626e4ff1be8305.91108394-original.jpg",
    "thumbnail": "https://en.numista.com/catalogue/photos/ukraine/626e4ff1be8305.91108394-180.jpg",
    "picture_copyright": "hex7ech",
    "picture_license_name": "CC BY-NC",
    "picture_license_url": "https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/deed.en"
  },
  "comments": "<p>UV activity:<br><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/64f224d7f24c2.png\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/64f224d7f24c2.png\" alt=\"\"></a><br>© gyoschak</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>UV activity (2005, P#117b):</p><p><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/6668f7f3c584f.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/6668f7f3c584f.jpg\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/6668f7f45156e.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/6668f7f45156e.jpg\"></a></p><p>© Kiet Tran</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p style=\"margin-left:0px;\">Security thread:</p><p style=\"margin-left:0px;\">Solid, only visible under a backlight with the inscription of “2 ГРН” repeated twice as well as the national emblem.</p><p style=\"margin-left:0px;\"><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/6668f7a07dbfe.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/6668f7a07dbfe.jpg\"></a></p><p style=\"margin-left:0px;\">© Kiet Tran<br><br>Volodymyr Semenovych Stelmakh was Chairman (Governor) of the Bank of Ukraine from 2000 until 2002 and from 2004 until 2010<br>Serhiy Leonidovych Tihipko was Chairman (Governor) of the Bank of Ukraine from 2002 until 2004<br>Serhiy Hennadiiovych Arbuzov was Chairman (Governor) of the Bank of Ukraine from 2010 until 2012<br>Ihor Viacheslavovych Sorkin was Chairman (Governor) of the Bank of Ukraine from 2013 until 2014<br>Yakiv Vasylovych Smoliy was Chairman (Governor) of the Bank of Ukraine from 2018 until July 3, 2020</p>",
